Before you start with the shooting, we recommend you to decide what method want to use, either the "Fixed Point Method" or the "Imaginary Line Method". There is a third method that is more experimental and not so common, we'll call it "Stop Motion Method".\
So, what is the difference? It\'92s basically that in the first method, the camera maintains a point of reference from the beginning to the end at the same position. In the second one the camera maintains its position by imagining a straight line and mainlining it with the tripod. We'll explain which method is more convenient in which situation and show some examples of each.\
